    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "that's a pretty bleak outlook. but wouldn't proponents argue that those same tax cuts actually help inequality by stimulating the economy and creating jobs for everyone? i'm trying to understand why most analysts are leaning towards the \"widening gap\" conclusion instead of the growth argument.",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
